data.name: lblQualification.Text
data.value: The BeginQualification method will trigger the qualifiers that have been defined in your partner configuration file. As this method may take up to twenty seconds (depending on the number of qualifiers and the response time of the external services), it is suggested that your application waits for a at least one minute before calling GetQualificationResult().

data.name: lblCreateApplication.Text
data.value:
Commerce Boarding offers connectivity to several external services. As you design your application and determine which services you would like to consume, your Solutions Consultant at IP Commerce will provide you with a list of data elements to send to the IP Commerce Platform on an application.
Once your specific needs are defined, your Customer Experience Engineer will create a configuration for your application on the IP Commerce Platforn, then give you an Application Profile Id for identification.

data.name: label7.Text
data.value: Identity Verification is an optional service which will confirm that the end user is who they claim to be. The Commerce Boarding Service will retrieve a list of questions from the Identity Verification service which only the user will know the answers for.
